00:14:47.024 --> 00:14:50.544
machine, a separate Mac mini or whatever,
then of

00:14:50.584 --> 00:14:54.324
course, anything bad
that happens there stays on that machine.

00:14:54.424 --> 00:14:57.804
So that might be worth it
and you have a better separation.

00:14:58.244 --> 00:15:02.144
And, uh, for example,
your tax documents

00:15:02.164 --> 00:15:06.104
machine wouldn't be, uh, accessible

00:15:06.264 --> 00:15:09.724
on your development machine.
So having that separation might

00:15:09.764 --> 00:15:13.704
be, uh, worth a look.
If you don't have a separate machine

00:15:13.843 --> 00:15:17.104
use it,
you could look into using a virtual

